rd object\n3. **Version Sequencing**: Migrations are applied sequentially from current version to target version\n4. **Schema Versioning**: Version 42 is final - no new schema versions are added; panel-specific migrations are handled by panel plugins\n5. **Datasource Handling**: V33 and V36 migrations require datasource information, using DataSourceInfoProvider interface\n6. **Default Values Management**: Frontend defaults are applied before migrations to ensure consistent behavior\n7. **Cleanup Phase**: Post-migration cleanup removes non-persisted properties and null values to match save model behavior\n\nThe system successfully bridges frontend and backend implementations, ensuring that dashboards can be reliably migrated through 40+ schema versions while maintaining consistency and data integrity across the Grafana ecosystem."
